VSanjay Guha from Kolkata is performing a sitar recital at New Delhi&#8217;s India Habitat Centre this Friday. Sanjay, claimed to be &#8220;the first sitar artist to be awarded a fellowship by Trinity College London&#8221;, is performing at IHC as a part of HCL Concert Series.Guha&#8217;s musical tutelage began at an early age under the guidance of his uncle Satyabrat Guha (disciple of the late Pandit Balram Pathak). Later, he received training from the sarod maestro late Pandit Radhikamohan Maitra. From 1980 he also received guidance from late Pandit Deepak Choudhury of Maihar-Senia gharana.In 2004, Guha was awarded one of the most prestigious awards, the Baba Allauddin Khan Smriti Samman from Mangal Dhwani in Delhi and the Ustad Faiyyaz Khan Anandi award from Anandi music circle in Kolkata.(The performance starts at 7.p.m.)
